/* ================================================================
   gopher-iq-data.js - Gopher iQ shared data layer ("the data brain")
   ----------------------------------------------------------------
   Single source of truth for location COVERAGE that Gopher iQ reads
   from (and that other pages/functions can read too, over time).
   (load gopher-iq-data.js first, then the Gopher iQ engine)

   Derived from Users_02_07_2026.csv + Orders_02_07_2026.csv, with ZIP
   coordinates from GeoNames (https://www.geonames.org/, CC BY 4.0).

   A "worker" (local, ENGAGED Gopher) = a user whose role includes
   "Gopher", whose Gopher Stripe payout is VERIFIED, whose account is
   ACTIVE, AND who is engaged -- i.e. signed up in the last 6 months
   OR has completed at least 1 request all-time. (The engagement gate
   keeps the count from being inflated by registrations that never
   actually worked the platform.)
   "activeLast3mo" = distinct Gophers who COMPLETED (delivered) a request
   in the last ~3 months (from the Orders report). Both counts are a
   10-MILE RADIUS around the queried place (what actually drives the odds
   a request gets accepted), not just the exact city. State is taken from
   the ZIP via GeoNames (the report's own state field is unreliable).
   Each entry is [workers, activeLast3mo].

   >>> TODO (production): replace these static tables with a live query
   to the production database (or a small coverage API). Keep the public
   shape (GopherIQData.lookup) identical so nothing downstream changes.
   ================================================================ */
